Class PrefixFluent

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.Fluent
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.comp.PrefixFluent
All Implemented Interfaces:
Expression, Logical, Simplifiable, Typed, Signed, Serializable, Comparable<Logical>
public class PrefixFluent extends Fluent
A special fluent object that may be created when reasoning about beliefs and compiled fluents.

Because compiled fluents have ID numbers which indicate their index in a compiled problem's set of fluents, new compiled fluents cannot be added to a compiled problem after it is created. However, the CompiledFluent.prepend(Parameter) method still needs to return something, so a prefix fluent is a special object representing a compiled fluent (or another prefix fluent) to which an character has been prepended when such a fluent does not exist in the compiled problem.

Author:
Stephen G. Ware
